_______________________________________________________________________________


Chunky Maze is a demo of a Wolfenstein engine for Amigas equipped with 68020+
and AGA chipset

v1.02 contains the following features:

* True perspective texture-mapping
* Variable window width & height
* Variable chunkiness (can go as low as 1x1)
* Mouse OR joystick control
* Depth cueing option
* PAL and NTSC support

_______________________________________________________________________________

                                INSTRUCTIONS

You can use the Mouse or the joystick to move about this maze, but I recommend
the mouse.

Press RIGHT MOUSE BUTTON to pop up the prefs window, where you can alter window
dimensions, chunkiness, and toggle depth-cueing.

LEFT MOUSE BUTTON or FIRE on the joystick exits the demo

NOTE! This demo uses the Copper to emulate a chunky screen display, therefore
screen dimensions are limited by the hardware.

Feel free to contact me about this demo.

